text: Park Mi-hee (born 10 December 1963) is a South Korean volleyball player, and coach. She played at the 1984 Summer Olympics, 1988 Summer Olympics, 1982 Asian Games, 1990 Asian Games, and 1990 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She played for Midopa. She coached for Incheon Heungkuk Life Pink Spiders. == References == Category:1963 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean volleyball players Category:Volleyball coaches Category:Olympians for South Korea
